  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati&nbsp;</strong><strong>rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>&nbsp;<strong>shallots</strong>&nbsp;(you'll use the rest later!)&nbsp;and all of the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon)</p>\r\n<p>Cut the stalks off the <strong>coriander</strong>&nbsp;and set the leaves aside for later &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the stalk off of the <strong>red&nbsp;chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>coriander stalks</strong>, <strong>chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)&nbsp;and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> and blitz the lot to a coarse paste&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you don't have a food processor, just chop everything together finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> curry powder&nbsp;</strong>and <strong>ground&nbsp;</strong><strong>turmeric</strong> and cook for 1 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the blended ingredients, with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant and softened</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the hard&nbsp;<strong>coconut</strong><strong>&nbsp;cream</strong> into pieces and combine it with 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water </strong>and whisk to dissolve - this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Separate the <strong>white crabmeat</strong> from the<strong> brown crabmeat</strong>, you'll use the white meat later!</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock,</strong> 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and the <strong>brown crabmeat</strong> to the pan and cook for 5 min or until it's reached a loose consistency</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, halve the <strong>cucumber</strong> lengthways, scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon and discard, then finely slice the flesh</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> leaves roughly</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the remaining&nbsp;<strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Halve the <strong>lime</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mix the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>cucumber</strong>, <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>shallot </strong>and&nbsp;<strong>nigella seeds&nbsp;</strong>in a bowl&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Squeeze&nbsp;the juice of the <strong>lime</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> into the bowl and add and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>- this is your <strong>cucumber salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sri-lankan-crab-curry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curry</strong> in bowls with the cooked <strong>rice</strong> and garnish with the <strong>white crabmeat</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: for fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p>\r\n<p>Serve the <strong>cucumber salad</strong> alongside</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!<br /><br /></p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
